<body>
    <h1>Data Warehousing</h1>
    <div class=3D"Section1">
        <h1 id=3D"DataWarehousing-ClickHouseDataWarehouse&amp;ExportIntegra=
tion=E2=80=93Architecture&amp;ImplementationGuide">ClickHouse Data Warehous=
e &amp; Export Integration =E2=80=93 Architecture &amp; Implementation Guid=
e</h1>
<p><strong>Owner:</strong> Data Platform Team<br><strong>Prepared for:</str=
ong> Siva / CultureMonkey engineering<br><strong>Last updated:</strong> 202=
5=E2=80=9109=E2=80=9102</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-1)ExecutiveSummary">1) Executive Summary</h2>
<p>This document proposes a production=E2=80=91grade data warehousing solut=
ion on <strong>ClickHouse</strong> that powers analytics and customer-facin=
g data exports (CSV/Parquet feeds, S3 drops, Kafka streams, and JDBC/ODBC f=
or BI tools). It includes multi=E2=80=91tenant isolation, scalable ingestio=
n, transformations, performance tuning, security, and a reference =E2=80=9C=
Export Service=E2=80=9D design to deliver per-tenant datasets on demand or =
on schedule.</p>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-2)Goals&amp;Non=E2=80=91Goals">2) Goals &amp; Non=
=E2=80=91Goals</h2>
<p><strong>Goals</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Centralize survey/feedback data (200K+ employees, 120K+ feedback/day bur=
sts) in ClickHouse.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Sub=E2=80=91second analytics for dashboards; batch exports within minute=
s.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Multi=E2=80=91tenant isolation with row policies and schema design.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>Turnkey export channels: CSV/Parquet to S3, JDBC/ODBC for BI, and push f=
eeds via Kafka.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Cost=E2=80=91efficient storage with S3 integration, tiering, and partiti=
oning.</p></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Non=E2=80=91Goals</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Full replacement of OLTP systems.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Advanced ML feature store (can be layered later).</p></li>
</ul>
<hr>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-3)High=E2=80=91LevelArchitecture">3) High=E2=80=
=91Level Architecture</h2>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Sources:</strong> App DBs (Postgres/MySQL), event streams (Kafka=
), files (CSV/Parquet), 3rd=E2=80=91party tools.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Ingestion:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p><em>Change Data Capture (CDC):</em> Debezium =E2=86=92 Kafka (Avro/JSON)=
 =E2=86=92 ClickHouse <code>Kafka</code> engine.</p></li>
<li>
<p><em>Batch Loads:</em> Parquet in S3 =E2=86=92 <code>s3</code> table func=
tion / <code>S3</code> engine =E2=86=92 <code>INSERT SELECT</code>.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p><em>Direct:</em> HTTP <code>INSERT</code> for small/real=E2=80=91time re=
cords.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Landing (Raw):</strong> <code>MergeTree</code>/<code>ReplacingMe=
rgeTree</code> per domain table partitioned by month.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Transform:</strong> Materialized Views (MVs) build columnar, que=
ry=E2=80=91optimized marts.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Serving:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Ad=E2=80=91hoc/OLAP queries via ClickHouse.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Export Service for CSV/Parquet generation and managed sharing.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Kafka topics for push feeds to customers.</p></li>
<li>
<p>JDBC/ODBC for BI tools (Tableau, Power BI).</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Storage:</strong> Local NVMe for hot parts; S3 for cold parts vi=
a <code>S3</code>/<code>S3ObjectStorage</code> and tiering.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Orchestration:</strong> Airflow/Dagster (batch) + Kafka streamin=
g (real=E2=80=91time).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Security:</strong> RBAC users/roles, Row Policies by <code>tenan=
t_id</code>, TLS, customer=E2=80=91scoped credentials.</p></li>
</ul>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-4)DataModel(SurveyDomain=E2=80=93Reference)">4) D=
ata Model (Survey Domain =E2=80=93 Reference)</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-4.1CoreEntities">4.1 Core Entities</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>tenants</strong>(tenant_id, name, status, plan, created_at)</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p><strong>employees</strong>(tenant_id, employee_id, email, manager_id, at=
tributes=E2=80=A6)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>surveys</strong>(tenant_id, survey_id, name, type, language, lau=
nched_at)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>questions</strong>(tenant_id, survey_id, question_id, type, text=
, options_json)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>submissions</strong>(tenant_id, submission_id, survey_id, employ=
ee_id, submitted_at, channel, device)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>answers</strong>(tenant_id, submission_id, question_id, answer_v=
alue, answer_text, answer_json)</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>sentiment</strong>(tenant_id, submission_id, score, magnitude, t=
opics_array, model_version)</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-4.2ClickHouseStorageEngines">4.2 ClickHouse Stora=
ge Engines</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><code>MergeTree</code> for immutable facts (submissions, answers) with m=
onthly partitions.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>ReplacingMergeTree(version)</code> when late updates or correction=
s are possible.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>AggregatingMergeTree</code> for pre=E2=80=91aggregated marts (ENPS=
 by segment, time).</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-5)IngestionPatterns">5) Ingestion Patterns</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-5.1StreamingviaKafka">5.1 Streaming via Kafka</h3=
>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>CDC:</strong> Debezium on Postgres =E2=86=92 Kafka topics (<code=
>survey.submissions</code>, <code>survey.answers</code>).</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>ClickHouse:</strong> <code>Kafka</code> engine tables + MVs to l=
and in <code>MergeTree</code>.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-5.2BatchviaS3Parquet">5.2 Batch via S3 Parquet</h=
3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Land hourly/daily Parquet files in <code>s3://cm-raw/survey/answers/ym=
=3DYYYYMM/=E2=80=A6</code>.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Load using <code>INSERT SELECT</code>:</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-5.3DirectHTTPInserts(micro-events)">5.3 Direct HT=
TP Inserts (micro-events)</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>For small, real=E2=80=91time streams where Kafka is overkill.</p></li>
<li>
<p><code>POST /?query=3DINSERT INTO cm_dw.events FORMAT JSONEachRow</code> =
with auth &amp; TLS.</p></li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-6)Multi=E2=80=91TenantIsolation&amp;Security">6) =
Multi=E2=80=91Tenant Isolation &amp; Security</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-6.1RBAC&amp;RowPolicies">6.1 RBAC &amp; Row Polic=
ies</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Use <strong>separate users/roles per tenant</strong> for direct BI/JDBC =
access.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Optionally add <strong>column masking</strong> for PII (e.g., hash email=
s) via views.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-6.2Network&amp;Auth">6.2 Network &amp; Auth</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>TLS for client =E2=86=92 server.</p></li>
<li>
<p>mTLS for internal services; IP allowlists for customer connections.</p><=
/li>
<li>
<p>Secrets in Vault/SSM; short=E2=80=91lived creds where possible.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-6.3Compliance">6.3 Compliance</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Tag PII columns; encrypt at rest (disk + S3).</p></li>
<li>
<p>Data subject deletion =3D delete/overwrite in OLTP =E2=86=92 emit CDC to=
mbstones =E2=86=92 propagate to CH with Replacing/Collapsing strategy.</p><=
/li>
</ul>
<p></p>
<h2 id=3D"DataWarehousing-7)ExportIntegrationOptions">7) Export Integration=
 Options</h2>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-7.1Self=E2=80=91ServeBI(Pull)">7.1 Self=E2=80=91S=
erve BI (Pull)</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>JDBC/ODBC</strong>: Provision tenant=E2=80=91scoped users/roles =
+ Row Policies.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Tools:</strong> Tableau, Power BI, Superset, Metabase.</p></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Pros:</strong> zero data movement. <strong>Cons:</strong> live q=
uery cost &amp; governance.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-7.2ManagedFileExports(PushorOn=E2=80=91Demand)">7=
.2 Managed File Exports (Push or On=E2=80=91Demand)</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p><strong>Formats:</strong> CSV, Parquet (recommended), JSONLines.</p></li=
>
<li>
<p><strong>Delivery:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Write to internal S3 bucket then <strong>share via pre=E2=80=91signed UR=
L</strong> or cross=E2=80=91account S3 access.</p></li>
<li>
<p>Optional delivery to customer SFTP.</p></li>
</ul></li>
<li>
<p><strong>Implementation:</strong> Export Service (below) or <code>clickho=
use-local</code> for big, offline extracts.</p></li>
</ul>
<h3 id=3D"DataWarehousing-7.3StreamingFeeds(Push)">7.3 Streaming Feeds (Pus=
h)</h3>
<ul>
<li>
<p>Publish curated topics (e.g., <code>export.enps_monthly</code>, <code>ex=
port.answers</code>) to <strong>Kafka</strong>; customers consume and load =
to their DW.</p></li>
</ul>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
